After a servlet includes a jsp , which can modify the request attribute, by
using RequestDispacher.include(request, response), the attributes are not
modified. 

Test case codes:

public class ServletContextGetRequestDispatcherTestServlet extends HttpServlet {

/**
 *	We will try to get the RequestDispatcher for this servlet
 *	itself
 */

public void service (HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response)
throws ServletException, IOException {

		PrintWriter out = response.getWriter();

		String path="/jsp/ModifyRequestAttribute.jsp" ;


		ServletConfig config = this.getServletConfig();
		ServletContext context = config.getServletContext();

		RequestDispatcher rd = context.getRequestDispatcher(path);


                if(rd != null)  {
                        rd.include(request,response) ;
			String getted = (String)request.getAttribute("Attributeadd1");
			out.println("Getted attribute value =" + getted);

//here, servlet gets "null" !

                }
                else {
                        out.println("ServletContextGetRequestDispatcherTest test
FAILED <BR>");
                        out.println("Request Dispatcher Couldn't forward to jsp
");
                }
	}
}



